      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, the veto power definitely seems like a huge bottleneck. but do historians see that as an inherent flaw in the UN's design that makes it basically obsolete, or is it more that the organization is just working as intended given how difficult global diplomacy is these days?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
