      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The current consensus among historians is that the veto power is an inherent, structural flaw that fundamentally limits the UN's ability to act decisively. It is not a sign of the organization working \"as intended,\" but rather a demonstration of its foundational weakness created during the Cold War era. Because the UN was designed to balance the interests of great powers, it inherently lacks the necessary enforcement mechanism to stop conflicts when those powers disagree.",
